result.formatted_address: 198 Junction Rd, Wang Tau Hom, Hong Kong
result.name: Azabu Sabo

reviews.text:
wowwow, in a mall cafe with  good quality. 
 All of their Japanese pot, steak and other food items are served hot like it's freshly cooked. 
The presentation of the entrees is just beautiful!
 We really love their potstickers and Japanese soups. Their unique Japanese style desserts are both pretty to look at and very refreshing.

Ordered the cold noodle soba set and was alright with the portion size. They could have given a little bit more soba but I'll take what I can get during lunch time. The soba included a small rice dish with beef an onion. There was an ice cream included at the lunch set at the end. I got the ice cream with sesame at the bottom. There was a purple yam under the ice cream which was kind of weird but I grew to like it.
Nice place for lunch
It's ok, but quite expensive
The food is very good but the prices are a bit expensive.

result.adr_address: 香港橫頭磡聯合道198號
result.name: 麻布茶房

reviews.text:
食物麻麻！
服務態度差極！
只是要求一杯水，這個長髪扎馬尾的女侍應，好兇惡的回答，妳自己出去斟。當時只得四五個客人，估唔到連斟水的服務也沒有。
這位女侍應跟著更不斷惡言惡語地話我自己唔去斟，話我望住佢。
竟然一間連鎖店的餐廳，有這些趕客的侍應。

火鍋抵食
其他飯類套餐唔建議！超過$100但餸比茶餐廳更差
上菜時間快，食物質素尚算理想，座位距離很近，環境較少私隱，價錢稍貴。
食品同服務在同區內中規中舉
我叫左一個牛柳粒嘅lunch set， 牛柳粒好咸牛肉好鞋 同埋份量唔多， 唔值100蚊嘅價錢 。本身入去之前見到lunch set有haagen dazs雪糕， 所以先入去，但最後入到去先發現無曬雪榚。 入面有一個中年嘅waiter ，服務態度好差，冇禮貌，一直黑面。同埋無諗過靜係收現金.... 宇治金時紫薯雪糕幾好食!

result.adr_address: 77 Ngau Tau Kok Rd, Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 77 Ngau Tau Kok Rd, Kowloon Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Amoy Plaza

reviews.text: Old private estate shopping mall struggling to compete with new ones.  It is not the new huge malls with high ceilings big brands but you may like the surprises and the rare shops at the corners or far end of corridors.  There are a few shops selling expert model kits for adults and toys for teenagers and game console games also.
Many good restaurants, many hobby stores. Something for everyone. Best of all, affordable price.
Many delicious food such as Genki Sushi and Pizza Hut

A lot of choices to choose from, a cinema and stuff like that. What you would hope from a decent shopping mall. There are also housing estates above the shopping centre but ofc it's too expensive for a normal human being in Hong Kong to afford
Nice concentrated shops and diversity.
